.TH HYPRSUNSET 1 "2025-11-07" "hyprsunset 0.3.3" "Hyprland Ecosystem"
.SH NAME
hyprsunset \- blue\-light filter for Hyprland
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hyprsunset
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hyprsunset
is a utility to apply a blue\-light filter on displays managed by Hyprland.
It uses the hyprland\-ctm\-control\-v1 Wayland protocol, making it specific to
Hyprland.
.PP
Unlike screen shader approaches, the color temperature adjustment is not
captured in recordings or screenshots.
.B hyprsunset
also supports gamma adjustment for controlling perceived display brightness.
.PP
Requires Hyprland 0.45.0 or later.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-temperature " " \fIkelvin\fR
Set the color temperature in Kelvin. Default: 6000.
Lower values produce a warmer (more orange) color.
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-gamma " " \fIpercent\fR
Set display gamma as a percentage. Default: 100.
.TP
.BR \-\-gamma_max " " \fIpercent\fR
Set maximum display gamma as a percentage. Default: 200.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-identity
Use identity matrix (no color change), effectively disabling the filter.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIpath\fR
Specify a custom configuration file path.
.TP
.BR \-\-verbose
Enable trace logging.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is searched for at
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/hypr/hyprsunset.conf
or
.IR ~/.config/hypr/hyprsunset.conf .
A configuration file is not required.
.SS General options
.TP
.B max\-gamma
Maximum display gamma percentage. Default: 100.
.SS Profile section (repeatable)
Time\-based profiles allow automatic color temperature transitions:
.TP
.B time
Time of day in HH:MM format.
.TP
.B temperature
Color temperature in Kelvin. Default: 6000.
.TP
.B gamma
Gamma multiplier. Default: 1.0.
.SH EXAMPLES
Set a warm color temperature for evening use:
.PP
.RS
.B hyprsunset \-t 4000
.RE
.PP
Reduce gamma to 80%:
.PP
.RS
.B hyprsunset \-g 80
.RE
.SH SYSTEMD INTEGRATION
.B hyprsunset
ships with a systemd user service:
.PP
.RS
.B systemctl \-\-user enable \-\-now hyprsunset.service
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR Hyprland (1),
.BR hyprctl (1)
